23/12/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Albania and the United Kingdom will exchange information on crime affecting the two countries, according to an agreement signed on Wednesday (December 22nd).
Interior Minister Lulzim Basha described the deal as another step in the government's commitment to showing zero tolerance towards organised crime.
During the ceremony, UK Ambassador to Tirana Fiona Mcllwham praised the progress made by Albanian police, and pledged to support the country's continuing efforts to strengthen the rule of law.
(Lajmifundit, NOA, Telegrafi, Balkan Web - 22/12/10)
